attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles a table. He first disassembles the wheels, then unscrews the tray and removes it, then tries to unscrew the bars from the table, and repeats the above process with each tray in the rolling cart. Finally, He unscrew the sidebars and put everything on the table.

attributes.Transcription: Okay, now please disassemble this shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student loosens the lower wheels.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student turns the wrench in the wrong direction.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should use both hexagonal wrenches to slightly loosen the wheels.

attributes.Transcription: Please use both to slightly loosen the wheels.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student turns the wrench in the wrong direction.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the lower wheels.
The student disassembles the center tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should keep the structure laying down to the boxes.

attributes.Transcription: Please keep the structure laying down to the boxes.
You should start removing the middle box.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the upper tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student turns the wrench in the wrong direction.
The student turns the hexagon cap nut in the wrong direction.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the black trays.
The student disassembles the lower tray.

attributes.Transcription: You can make in this structure stand up again to remove the other box.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should make this structure stand up again to remove the other box.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the black side bars from the base frame.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student switches to the lower joint at the instructor's suggestion.

attributes.Transcription: Please start by removing the bottom screw first.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the black base frame.
The student disassembles the first side bar.
The student disassembles the second side bar.

attributes.Transcription: You can press the stop button.
